Pop musician, Peter Okoye, one half of defunct Nigerian music duo, P-Square, has celebrated deceased musical icon, Michael Jackson, 10 years after death. Tuesday marks the 10th anniversary of Jackson’s death. The 37-year-old singer shared a picture of the man known as the King of Pop via Instagram. “10 years ago we lost an ICON. His legacy still lives on💔😫😩😭😢… We miss you dearly MJ❤️ #RIP,” he wrote. In their pomp, P-Square attempted some of the dance routines and dressings used by Michael Jackson, they released a song, ‘Personally,’ in tribute to him. Jermaine Jackson, brother of late pop music star, expressed profound gratitude to P-Square for recording a tribute song to the music legend. Source: QED